      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Another potential clue: the paint. Flecks of blue-green have been designed to only show up in sunlight. Rolls-Royce also used glow-in-the dark stitching throughout the interior. Owners are going to be literally going through every stitch of their car.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If someone thinks they’ve cracked the code, they can submit their theory to Rolls-Royce through the Whisper app. Only verified vehicle owners have access.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
